<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>HyperSpec Classifier — Land Cover Classification</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&family=DM+Sans:opsz,wght@9..40,300;9..40,400;9..40,500;9..40,600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <!-- ===== HEADER / NAVIGATION ===== -->
  <header>
    <div class="logo">
      <div class="logo-dot"></div>
      HyperSpec Classifier
    </div>
    <nav>
      <a href="#map-section">Map Viewer</a>
      <a href="#comparison-section">Compare</a>
      <a href="#legend-section">Legend</a>
      <a href="#about-section">About</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <!-- ===== HERO SECTION ===== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">

      <div class="hero-text fade-up d1">
        <div class="hero-badge">
          <span>●</span>&nbsp;AVIRIS · Indian Pines · 145×145 · 200 Bands
        </div>
        <h1>Land Cover<br><span>Classification</span><br>System</h1>
        <p>
          Hyperspectral image analytics using SVM, Random Forest and CNN.
          Each pixel in the image is classified into one of 16 land cover types
          based on its unique spectral signature across 200 wavelength bands.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-val">200</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Spectral Bands</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-val">16</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Land Classes</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-val">92.1%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Best Accuracy</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-map fade-up d2">
        <div class="corner corner-tl"></div>
        <div class="corner corner-tr"></div>
        <div class="corner corner-bl"></div>
        <div class="corner corner-br"></div>
        <img id="hero-gt-img" src="" alt="Ground Truth Classification Map" />
        <div class="hero-map-label">Ground Truth Map · Indiana, USA</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== MAIN CONTENT ===== -->
  <main>

    <!-- SECTION 1 — MAP VIEWER -->
    <section id="map-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">01</span>
        <span class="section-title">Classification Map Viewer</span>
        <div class="section-line"></div>
      </div>

      <p class="section-desc">
        Select a model to see how it classifies every pixel in the 145×145 image.
        Each colour represents a different land cover type.
        <strong>Scroll to zoom in</strong> and inspect individual fields and crop boundaries.
        Compare against the Ground Truth to see where each model succeeds or makes mistakes.
      </p>

      <!-- Model Selector Tabs -->
      <div class="model-tabs" role="tablist">
        <button class="model-tab active" onclick="selectModel('svm')" id="tab-svm" role="tab" aria-selected="true">
          SVM <span class="badge">92.1%</span>
        </button>
        <button class="model-tab" onclick="selectModel('rf')" id="tab-rf" role="tab" aria-selected="false">
          Random Forest <span class="badge">86.63%</span>
        </button>
        <button class="model-tab" onclick="selectModel('cnn')" id="tab-cnn" role="tab" aria-selected="false">
          CNN <span class="badge">91.15%</span>
        </button>
      </div>

      <!-- Metrics Strip -->
      <div class="metrics-strip" id="metrics-strip">
        <div class="mcard lit">
          <div class="mcard-val" id="m-acc">92.1%</div>
          <div class="mcard-label">Accuracy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mcard lit">
          <div class="mcard-val" id="m-prec">92.06%</div>
          <div class="mcard-label">Precision</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mcard lit">
          <div class="mcard-val" id="m-rec">92.1%</div>
          <div class="mcard-label">Recall</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mcard lit">
          <div class="mcard-val" id="m-f1">92.06%</div>
          <div class="mcard-label">F1-Score</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mcard lit">
          <div class="mcard-val" id="m-kappa">0.9099</div>
          <div class="mcard-label">Kappa</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Side-by-side Map Panels -->
      <div class="map-compare">

        <!-- Ground Truth -->
        <div class="map-panel">
          <div class="map-panel-header">
            <span class="map-panel-title">Ground Truth (Reference)</span>
            <span class="map-panel-tag">Actual Labels</span>
          </div>
          <div class="zoom-container" id="zoom-gt"
               onwheel="handleZoom(event,'gt')"
               onmousedown="startDrag(event,'gt')"
               onmousemove="doDrag(event,'gt')"
               onmouseup="stopDrag('gt')"
               onmouseleave="stopDrag('gt')"
               ontouchstart="startTouchDrag(event,'gt')"
               ontouchmove="doTouchDrag(event,'gt')"
               ontouchend="stopDrag('gt')">
            <img id="img-gt" src="" alt="Ground Truth Map" />
            <div class="zoom-hint">Scroll to zoom · Drag to pan</div>
          </div>
          <div class="zoom-controls">
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="zoomIn('gt')">＋</button>
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="zoomOut('gt')">－</button>
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="resetZoom('gt')">Reset</button>
            <span class="zoom-level" id="zoom-level-gt">1×</span>
            <span class="zoom-info">145 × 145 px</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Predicted Map -->
        <div class="map-panel">
          <div class="map-panel-header">
            <span class="map-panel-title">Predicted Classification Map</span>
            <span class="map-panel-tag" id="active-tag">SVM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="zoom-container" id="zoom-pred"
               onwheel="handleZoom(event,'pred')"
               onmousedown="startDrag(event,'pred')"
               onmousemove="doDrag(event,'pred')"
               onmouseup="stopDrag('pred')"
               onmouseleave="stopDrag('pred')"
               ontouchstart="startTouchDrag(event,'pred')"
               ontouchmove="doTouchDrag(event,'pred')"
               ontouchend="stopDrag('pred')">
            <img id="img-pred" src="" alt="Predicted Classification Map" />
            <div class="zoom-hint">Scroll to zoom · Drag to pan</div>
          </div>
          <div class="zoom-controls">
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="zoomIn('pred')">＋</button>
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="zoomOut('pred')">－</button>
            <button class="zoom-btn" onclick="resetZoom('pred')">Reset</button>
            <span class="zoom-level" id="zoom-level-pred">1×</span>
            <button class="zoom-btn sync-btn" onclick="syncZoom()">Sync Zoom</button>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div><!-- end map-compare -->

      <!-- Per-Class Accuracy Bar Chart -->
      <div class="perclass-panel">
        <div class="perclass-title">
          Per-Class Accuracy — <span id="perclass-name">SVM</span>
        </div>
        <div id="bar-chart"></div>
      </div>

    </section><!-- end map-section -->

    <!-- SECTION 2 — COMPARISON TABLE -->
    <section id="comparison-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">02</span>
        <span class="section-title">Model Comparison</span>
        <div class="section-line"></div>
      </div>

      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Model</th>
            <th>Accuracy</th>
            <th>Precision</th>
            <th>Recall</th>
            <th>F1-Score</th>
            <th>Kappa</th>
            <th>Strength</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="model-name">Support Vector Machine <span class="winner-tag">BEST</span></td>
            <td class="best">92.1%</td>
            <td class="best">92.06%</td>
            <td class="best">92.1%</td>
            <td class="best">92.06%</td>
            <td class="best">0.9099</td>
            <td class="note">High-C boundary, stable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="model-name">Random Forest</td>
            <td>86.63%</td>
            <td>86.71%</td>
            <td>86.63%</td>
            <td>86.34%</td>
            <td>0.8467</td>
            <td class="note">Robust to noise</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="model-name">CNN (Deep Learning)</td>
            <td>91.15%</td>
            <td>90.87%</td>
            <td>91.15%</td>
            <td>90.93%</td>
            <td>0.8987</td>
            <td class="note">Spectral feature learning</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3 — LEGEND -->
    <section id="legend-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">03</span>
        <span class="section-title">Land Cover Class Legend</span>
        <div class="section-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="legend-panel">
        <p class="legend-desc">
          Each colour in the classification maps corresponds to one of the 16 land cover
          types found in the Indian Pines agricultural area. Match colours in the map to
          identify what the model predicted for that area.
        </p>
        <div class="legend-grid" id="legend-grid"></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4 — ABOUT -->
    <section id="about-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">04</span>
        <span class="section-title">About This System</span>
        <div class="section-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">🛰️</div>
          <h3>Dataset</h3>
          <p>Indian Pines hyperspectral dataset captured by AVIRIS sensor over northwestern Indiana, USA. 145×145 pixels, 200 spectral bands, covering 16 land cover classes including various crops, vegetation, and built structures.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">⚙️</div>
          <h3>Pipeline</h3>
          <p>Data preprocessed through StandardScaler normalization, background pixel removal, and 70/30 stratified train-test split. SVM uses RBF kernel with C=100. Random Forest uses 100 estimators. CNN uses two 1D convolutional layers trained for 50 epochs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">📈</div>
          <h3>Results</h3>
          <p>SVM achieves the highest accuracy of 92.1% (Kappa=0.9099), outperforming CNN at 91.15% and Random Forest at 86.63%. With proper hyperparameter tuning, SVM can outperform deep learning on smaller hyperspectral datasets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">🌍</div>
          <h3>Applications</h3>
          <p>Supports environmental monitoring, agricultural planning, and land-use policy decisions. The pipeline is modular and can be retrained on hyperspectral datasets from other regions such as Oman for local land cover mapping.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">🔬</div>
          <h3>Technology</h3>
          <p>Built with Python, scikit-learn, and PyTorch. Libraries: NumPy, SciPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn. Development in Google Colab. Dataset sourced from Purdue University's MultiSpec research group.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card">
          <div class="about-icon">🎓</div>
          <h3>Project Info</h3>
          <p>BSc (Hons) Computer Science final year project at Middle East College. Module: PROJS 30001.1. Supervisor: Dr. C. Jayakumari. Student: Anas Hameed, ID: 22F23425, Spring 2026.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <!-- ===== FOOTER ===== -->
  <footer>
    <div class="footer-left">
      HyperSpec Classifier ·
      <span>Land Cover Classification using Hyperspectral Image Data Analytics</span>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-right">
      Anas Hameed · 22F23425 · Middle East College · 2026
    </div>
  </footer>

  <!-- Scripts loaded at end of body -->
  <script src="js/data.js"></script>
  <script src="js/zoom.js"></script>
  <script src="js/app.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
